01:20:43.100 --> 01:20:45.580
- Like a big, frosted cupcake.
- I know, it's like...

01:20:47.180 --> 01:20:48.860
Come on, help me with the veil.

01:20:58.300 --> 01:20:59.940
- Hey.
- Yeah, you got it.

01:21:13.780 --> 01:21:15.220
Do we have to go in?

01:21:16.300 --> 01:21:17.860
Too late to elope now.

01:21:19.100 --> 01:21:20.380
Let's go in.

01:21:21.580 --> 01:21:22.620
Okay.

01:21:23.620 --> 01:21:24.700
Check this out.

01:21:25.940 --> 01:21:27.780
It's going down. Thank God.

01:21:28.140 --> 01:21:29.180
What?

01:21:29.260 --> 01:21:32.100
I woke up with this huge zit this morning.

01:21:33.260 --> 01:21:34.780
- Where?
- There.

01:21:34.860 --> 01:21:36.860
- I had a huge zit this morning.
- You did?

01:21:36.940 --> 01:21:38.180
- Yeah.
- Where is it?

01:21:38.260 --> 01:21:40.100
Well, it was right here. But it's gone.

01:21:40.140 --> 01:21:41.140
Why?

01:21:41.220 --> 01:21:42.740
I put some Windex on it.

01:22:18.340 --> 01:22:19.380
Hello.

01:22:23.300 --> 01:22:26.540
Welcome to the Portokalos family.

01:22:27.900 --> 01:22:29.980
And welcome...

01:22:30.060 --> 01:22:32.180
the Miller family.

01:22:33.460 --> 01:22:36.300
I was thinking, last night...

01:22:37.660 --> 01:22:39.420
the night before...

01:22:39.580 --> 01:22:43.140
my daughter was going to marry lan Miller...

01:22:43.740 --> 01:22:48.020
that the root of the word "miller"...

01:22:48.180 --> 01:22:49.260
is a Greek word.

01:22:49.580 --> 01:22:52.740
And "miller" come from...

01:22:52.820 --> 01:22:54.740
the Greek word milo...

01:22:55.060 --> 01:22:56.860
which is mean "apple. "

01:22:57.220 --> 01:22:58.180
There you go.

01:23:02.300 --> 01:23:04.220
As many of you know...

01:23:04.500 --> 01:23:06.340
our name Portokalos...

01:23:06.500 --> 01:23:09.220
is come from the Greek word portokali...

01:23:09.540 --> 01:23:11.420
which means "orange. "

01:23:11.940 --> 01:23:13.420
So, okay...

01:23:13.780 --> 01:23:15.020
here tonight...

01:23:15.140 --> 01:23:18.540
we have apple and orange.

01:23:20.860 --> 01:23:23.060
We all different...

01:23:23.700 --> 01:23:27.060
but, in the end, we all fruit.

01:23:31.300 --> 01:23:32.700
Yes, we are all fruit.

01:23:37.460 --> 01:23:39.660
My wife and me, we have a gift.

01:23:40.660 --> 01:23:42.780
That's what we do. The parents give a gift.

01:23:48.860 --> 01:23:49.900
Here.

01:23:56.700 --> 01:23:57.660
My God!

01:23:58.900 --> 01:24:00.300
They bought us a house.

01:24:33.940 --> 01:24:34.980
Thank you.

01:24:40.900 --> 01:24:41.900
I love you.

01:24:43.660 --> 01:24:44.940
I love you, too.

01:24:48.020 --> 01:24:49.540
I don't believe it.

01:24:50.180 --> 01:24:51.300
A house!

01:25:01.700 --> 01:25:03.460
Thia Voula, we're going to dance.

01:25:03.540 --> 01:25:05.980
- I know, dear. Let me get Taki.
- Okay.

01:25:06.180 --> 01:25:08.900
Athena, I'm going to be a painter.

01:25:09.100 --> 01:25:11.460
Good. You can start with our fence.

01:25:13.940 --> 01:25:16.660
This is just a really nice wedding.

01:25:16.740 --> 01:25:19.100
Good. We're going to dance now. Come on.

01:25:19.180 --> 01:25:20.100
No.

01:25:20.180 --> 01:25:22.700
I'll need a little more ouzo before I do that.

01:25:22.780 --> 01:25:24.420
What do you say?

01:25:27.340 --> 01:25:28.660
Bottoms up.

01:25:32.220 --> 01:25:33.860
- All right.
- Let's go, Harry.

01:25:35.940 --> 01:25:37.220
Come on, Kosta.

01:25:37.540 --> 01:25:39.420
All right.

01:25:43.540 --> 01:25:45.100
Oh, Taki.

01:25:46.020 --> 01:25:47.500
He looks Greek.

01:26:11.300 --> 01:26:12.780
Yia sou, lan.

01:26:20.940 --> 01:26:23.740
Sometimes, I'm afraid that it didn't happen.

01:26:23.780 --> 01:26:27.060
I'm scared I'll wake up
and still be buttering garlic bread...

01:26:27.140 --> 01:26:29.180
waiting for my life to start.

01:26:29.260 --> 01:26:31.140
But it did happen. It did!

01:26:31.460 --> 01:26:33.020
And I figured out some stuff.

01:26:33.220 --> 01:26:35.220
My family is big and loud...

01:26:35.500 --> 01:26:36.820
but they're my family.

01:26:36.940 --> 01:26:38.660
We fight and we laugh.

01:26:38.820 --> 01:26:41.380
And yes, we roast lamb on a spit
in the front yard.

01:26:41.940 --> 01:26:44.220
And wherever I go, whatever I do...

01:26:44.820 --> 01:26:46.460
they will always be there.

01:26:53.540 --> 01:26:56.740
So, lan and I moved into the house
my parents bought us.

01:26:57.100 --> 01:26:58.740
A minute later, I was pregnant.

01:26:58.820 --> 01:27:02.060
And six years later, it was our
daughter's turn to go to Greek school.

01:27:02.140 --> 01:27:04.220
Mom, I want to go to Brownies.

01:27:04.260 --> 01:27:06.500
I know, but I promise you this.

01:27:06.700 --> 01:27:09.060
You can marry anybody you want.

01:27:09.500 --> 01:27:11.300
Thanks, baby.

01:27:11.820 --> 01:27:13.060
Greek school, pame.

01:27:14.740 --> 01:27:15.700
What's that mean?

01:27:15.780 --> 01:27:16.740
"Let's go."

01:27:16.820 --> 01:27:18.420
- Let's go.
- That's pretty good.

01:27:18.500 --> 01:27:19.940
- Looking good, Gus.
- Hi, Dad.

01:27:20.020 --> 01:27:21.620
- Where you going?
- Greek school.

01:27:22.300 --> 01:27:23.260
Baklava!

